This notebook leverages Deep Machine Learning for Driver Drowsiness Detection¶

  • Implements a custom CNN architecture for drowsiness classification
  • Uses person based data splitting to prevent data leakage
  • Applies data augmentation with Albumentations
  • Includes early stopping and model checkpointing

Performing person based splitting¶

In [ ]:
import os
import shutil
import numpy as np
from pathlib import Path
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
from loguru import logger

def split_dataset_standard(
    drowsy_dir="../inputs/datasets/raw_cew/drowsy",
    non_drowsy_dir="../inputs/datasets/raw_cew/non_drowsy",
    out_root="../inputs/datasets/processed_cew",
    img_type="jpg",
    seed=1105086,
):
    for sub in ["train", "validation", "test"]:
        sub_dir = Path(out_root) / sub
        if sub_dir.exists():
            shutil.rmtree(sub_dir)
            logger.info(f"🧹 Cleared existing split folder: {sub_dir}")

    def gather(folder, label):
        return [(f, label) for f in Path(folder).glob(f"*.{img_type}")]

    drowsy = gather(drowsy_dir, "drowsy")
    non_drowsy = gather(non_drowsy_dir, "non_drowsy")
    all_files = drowsy + non_drowsy
    np.random.seed(seed)
    np.random.shuffle(all_files)

    file_paths = [f for f, _ in all_files]
    labels = [lbl for _, lbl in all_files]

    train_files, temp_files, train_labels, temp_labels = train_test_split(
        file_paths, labels, test_size=0.30, stratify=labels, random_state=seed
    )
    val_files, test_files, val_labels, test_labels = train_test_split(
        temp_files, temp_labels, test_size=0.50, stratify=temp_labels, random_state=seed
    )

    splits = {
        "train": list(zip(train_files, train_labels)),
        "validation": list(zip(val_files, val_labels)),
        "test": list(zip(test_files, test_labels)),
    }

    for split in splits:
        for lbl in ("drowsy", "non_drowsy"):
            os.makedirs(Path(out_root)/split/lbl, exist_ok=True)

    for split, files in splits.items():
        for f, lbl in files:
            tgt = Path(out_root)/split/lbl/f.name
            shutil.copy(f, tgt)

    logger.success("Dataset split complete.")
    for split, files in splits.items():
        d = sum(1 for _, lbl in files if lbl == "drowsy")
        nd = sum(1 for _, lbl in files if lbl == "non_drowsy")
        logger.info(f"{split.capitalize():<10} | Total: {len(files):<5} | Drowsy: {d:<4} | Non-drowsy: {nd:<4}")

    return {k: [f.name for f, _ in v] for k, v in splits.items()}

# Run it
ids_by_split = split_dataset_standard()
print(ids_by_split)

Albumentation transforms¶

  • Applies resizing to standardise input dimensions
  • HorizontalFlip mimics head position variations
  • RandomBrightnessContrast simulates different lighting conditions
  • GaussianBlur and GaussNoise increase robustness to image quality variations
  • Normalization prepares the images for neural network training
In [18]:
def get_training_transforms(
    img_size: tuple = (224, 224), grayscale: bool = True, normalize: bool = False
) -> A.Compose:
    transforms_list = [
        A.Resize(img_size[0], img_size[1]),
        A.HorizontalFlip(p=0.5),
        A.RandomBrightnessContrast(brightness_limit=0.15, contrast_limit=0.15, p=0.5),
        A.GaussianBlur(blur_limit=(1.0, 3.0), p=0.125),
        A.GaussNoise(var_limit=(0.1, 0.3), p=0.125),
    ]

    if normalize:
        if grayscale:
            transforms_list.append(A.Normalize(mean=[0.5], std=[0.5]))
        else:
            transforms_list.append(
                A.Normalize(mean=[0.485, 0.456, 0.406], std=[0.229, 0.224, 0.225])
            )

    transforms_list.append(ToTensorV2())
    return A.Compose(transforms_list)


def get_validation_transforms(
    img_size: tuple = (224, 224), grayscale: bool = True, normalize: bool = False
) -> A.Compose:
    transforms_list = [A.Resize(img_size[0], img_size[1])]

    if normalize:
        if grayscale:
            transforms_list.append(A.Normalize(mean=[0.5], std=[0.5]))
        else:
            transforms_list.append(
                A.Normalize(mean=[0.485, 0.456, 0.406], std=[0.229, 0.224, 0.225])
            )

    transforms_list.append(ToTensorV2())
    return A.Compose(transforms_list)


class AlbumentationsTransform:
    def __init__(self, transform):
        self.transform = transform

    def __call__(self, img):
        import numpy as np

        img = img.convert("L")
        img_array = np.array(img)
        augmented = self.transform(image=img_array)
        return augmented["image"].float()

ARCHITECTURE - fully defined within this cell¶

In [20]:
class DrowsinessDetectionCNN(nn.Module):
    def __init__(self, cfg: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None):
        super(DrowsinessDetectionCNN, self).__init__()

        if cfg is None:
            cfg = {
                "num_classes": 2,
                "dropout_rate": 0.4,
                "input_channels": 1,
                "input_height": 224,
                "input_width": 224,
            }

        self.in_ch = cfg["input_channels"]
        self.conv1 = nn.Conv2d(cfg["input_channels"], 8, kernel_size=3, padding=1)
        self.bn1 = nn.BatchNorm2d(8)
        self.conv2 = nn.Conv2d(8, 16, kernel_size=3, stride=1, padding=1)
        self.bn2 = nn.BatchNorm2d(16)
        self.conv3 = nn.Conv2d(16, 32, kernel_size=3, stride=1, padding=1)
        self.bn3 = nn.BatchNorm2d(32)

        self.pool = nn.MaxPool2d(2, 2)

        feature_h = cfg.get("input_height", 224) // 8
        feature_w = cfg.get("input_width", 224) // 8
        self.feat_size = 32 * feature_h * feature_w

        self.fc1 = nn.Linear(self.feat_size, 64)
        self.bn4 = nn.BatchNorm1d(64)
        self.fc2 = nn.Linear(64, 32)
        self.bn5 = nn.BatchNorm1d(32)
        self.fc3 = nn.Linear(32, cfg["num_classes"])

        self.dropout = nn.Dropout(cfg["dropout_rate"])

    def forward(self, x: torch.Tensor) -> torch.Tensor:
        x = self.pool(F.relu(self.bn1(self.conv1(x))))
        x = self.pool(F.relu(self.bn2(self.conv2(x))))
        x = self.pool(F.relu(self.bn3(self.conv3(x))))
        x = x.view(x.size(0), -1)
        x = self.dropout(F.relu(self.bn4(self.fc1(x))))
        x = self.dropout(F.relu(self.bn5(self.fc2(x))))
        x = self.fc3(x)
        return x

    def init_weights(self):
        for m in self.modules():
            if isinstance(m, nn.Conv2d):
                nn.init.kaiming_normal_(m.weight, mode="fan_out", nonlinearity="relu")
                if m.bias is not None:
                    nn.init.constant_(m.bias, 0)
            elif isinstance(m, nn.BatchNorm2d):
                nn.init.constant_(m.weight, 1)
                nn.init.constant_(m.bias, 0)
            elif isinstance(m, nn.Linear):
                nn.init.kaiming_normal_(m.weight, mode="fan_out", nonlinearity="relu")
                nn.init.constant_(m.bias, 0)

Model Trainer Script¶

In [23]:
class ModelTrainer:
    def __init__(
        self,
        model,
        train_loader,
        val_loader,
        criterion,
        optim,
        dev,
        best_ckpt_path,
        ckpt_dir="checkpoints",
        sched=None,
    ):
        self.model = model
        self.train_loader = train_loader
        self.val_loader = val_loader
        self.criterion = criterion
        self.optim = optim
        self.sched = sched
        self.dev = dev
        self.best_ckpt_path = best_ckpt_path
        self.ckpt_dir = ckpt_dir

        self.train_losses = []
        self.val_losses = []
        self.train_metrics = []
        self.val_metrics = []

        os.makedirs(self.ckpt_dir, exist_ok=True)

    def train(self, num_epochs=10, early_stop_patience=5):
        best_val_loss = np.inf
        patience_count = 0

        for epoch in range(num_epochs):
            train_loss, train_metrics = self._run_epoch(
                self.train_loader, training=True
            )
            val_loss, val_metrics = self._run_epoch(self.val_loader, training=False)

            self.train_losses.append(train_loss)
            self.val_losses.append(val_loss)
            self.train_metrics.append(train_metrics)
            self.val_metrics.append(val_metrics)

            logger.info(f"Epoch {epoch + 1}/{num_epochs}")
            logger.info(f"Train Loss: {train_loss:.4f}, Val Loss: {val_loss:.4f}")
            logger.info(
                f"Train Acc: {train_metrics['accuracy']:.4f}, Val Acc: {val_metrics['accuracy']:.4f}"
            )

            if val_loss < best_val_loss:
                best_val_loss = val_loss
                patience_count = 0
                torch.save(self.model.state_dict(), self.best_ckpt_path)
                logger.success("Best model saved.")
            else:
                patience_count += 1
                if patience_count >= early_stop_patience:
                    logger.warning("Early stopping triggered.")
                    break

            if self.sched:
                self.sched.step(val_loss)

    def _run_epoch(self, loader, training=True):
        if training:
            self.model.train()
        else:
            self.model.eval()

        running_loss = 0.0
        all_preds = []
        all_labels = []

        for imgs, labels in loader:
            imgs, labels = imgs.to(self.dev), labels.to(self.dev)

            if training:
                self.optim.zero_grad()

            with torch.set_grad_enabled(training):
                outputs = self.model(imgs)
                loss = self.criterion(outputs, labels)

                if training:
                    loss.backward()
                    self.optim.step()

            running_loss += loss.item() * imgs.size(0)
            preds = torch.argmax(outputs, dim=1)
            all_preds.extend(preds.detach().cpu().numpy())
            all_labels.extend(labels.detach().cpu().numpy())

        epoch_loss = running_loss / len(loader.dataset)
        metrics = self._compute_metrics(all_labels, all_preds)
        return epoch_loss, metrics

    def _compute_metrics(self, lbls, preds):
        return {
            "accuracy": accuracy_score(lbls, preds),
            "precision": precision_score(lbls, preds, zero_division=0),
            "recall": recall_score(lbls, preds, zero_division=0),
            "f1": f1_score(lbls, preds, zero_division=0),
        }

    train_loader=train_loader,

    optim=optim,
    dev=dev,
    ckpt_dir="../outputs/models/deep_ml/",

    sched=sched,
)

num_epochs = 100
early_stop_patience = 40

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt


def show_sample_images(dataloader, class_names, num_images=6):
    batch = next(iter(dataloader))
    images, labels = batch
    images = images[:num_images]
    labels = labels[:num_images]

    fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, num_images, figsize=(15, 3))
    for i, ax in enumerate(axes):
        img = images[i].squeeze().numpy()
        ax.imshow(img, cmap='gray')
        ax.set_title(f"Label: {class_names[labels[i]]}")
        ax.axis('off')

    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

class_names = train_ds.classes
show_sample_images(train_loader, class_names, num_images=6)

trainer.train(num_epochs=num_epochs, early_stop_patience=early_stop_patience)
checkpoint_path = (f"../outputs/models/deep_ml/checkpoints/TJM3_{timestamp}.pt",)

Saving model¶

In [25]:
timestamp = datetime.datetime.now().strftime("%Y%m%d_%H%M%S")
final_ckpt_path = f"../outputs/models/deep_ml/TJM3_FINAL_{timestamp}.pt"

torch.save(
    {
        "model_state": model.state_dict(),
        "optim_state": optim.state_dict(),
        "sched_state": sched.state_dict(),
        "train_losses": trainer.train_losses,
        "val_losses": trainer.val_losses,
        "train_metrics": trainer.train_metrics,
        "val_metrics": trainer.val_metrics,
    },
    final_ckpt_path,
)

logger.success(f"Final model checkpoint saved to {final_ckpt_path}")

Exporting training history to CSV format for analysis and visual production¶

In [26]:
data = []
for epoch in range(len(trainer.train_losses)):
    data.append(
        {
            "epoch": epoch + 1,
            "train_loss": trainer.train_losses[epoch],
            "val_loss": trainer.val_losses[epoch],
            "train_acc": trainer.train_metrics[epoch].get("accuracy", None),
            "train_prec": trainer.train_metrics[epoch].get("precision", None),
            "train_rec": trainer.train_metrics[epoch].get("recall", None),
            "train_f1": trainer.train_metrics[epoch].get("f1", None),
            "val_acc": trainer.val_metrics[epoch].get("accuracy", None),
            "val_prec": trainer.val_metrics[epoch].get("precision", None),
            "val_rec": trainer.val_metrics[epoch].get("recall", None),
            "val_f1": trainer.val_metrics[epoch].get("f1", None),
        }
    )

df = pd.DataFrame(data)
csv_path = f"../outputs/utils/deep_ml/training_history_csv_files/training_history_{timestamp}.csv"
df.to_csv(csv_path, index=False)
logger.success(f"Training history saved to {csv_path}")

Testing model on test set¶

In [27]:
best_ckpt_path = f"../outputs/models/deep_ml/TJM3_FINAL_{timestamp}.pt"
checkpoint = torch.load(best_ckpt_path)

model.load_state_dict(checkpoint["model_state"])
model.eval()
logger.success(f"Reloaded model weights from {best_ckpt_path}")

# Test set evaluation
all_preds = []
all_lbls = []

with torch.no_grad():
    for imgs, lbls in test_loader:
        imgs = imgs.to(dev)
        lbls = lbls.to(dev)

        outputs = model(imgs)
        preds = torch.argmax(outputs, dim=1)

        all_preds.extend(preds.cpu().numpy())
        all_lbls.extend(lbls.cpu().numpy())

# Compute metrics
test_acc = accuracy_score(all_lbls, all_preds)
test_prec = precision_score(all_lbls, all_preds, zero_division=0)
test_rec = recall_score(all_lbls, all_preds, zero_division=0)
test_f1 = f1_score(all_lbls, all_preds, zero_division=0)

# Log results
logger.info(f"Test Accuracy:  {test_acc:.4f}")
logger.info(f"Test Precision: {test_prec:.4f}")
logger.info(f"Test Recall:    {test_rec:.4f}")
logger.info(f"Test F1 Score:  {test_f1:.4f}")

logger.info("Classification Report:")
logger.info(f"\n{classification_report(all_lbls, all_preds, zero_division=0)}")

logger.info("Confusion Matrix:")
logger.info(f"\n{confusion_matrix(all_lbls, all_preds)}")

Plot Training vs. Validation Loss¶

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))
plt.plot(trainer.train_losses, label="Train Loss")
plt.plot(trainer.val_losses, label="Validation Loss")
plt.xlabel("Epoch")
plt.ylabel("Loss")
plt.title("Training vs. Validation Loss")
plt.legend()
plt.grid(True)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

GRAD-CAM¶

In [34]:
from captum.attr import LayerGradCam
from captum.attr import visualization as viz
from torchvision.transforms.functional import to_pil_image
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np
import torch

sample_img, sample_label = test_ds[0]
sample_img_tensor = sample_img.unsqueeze(0).to(dev)

model.eval()

target_layer = model.conv2 if hasattr(model, 'conv2') else model.base.layer4[-1]

gradcam = LayerGradCam(model, target_layer)

output = model(sample_img_tensor)
pred_class = output.argmax(dim=1).item()

attributions = gradcam.attribute(sample_img_tensor, target=pred_class)

attributions = torch.nn.functional.interpolate(
    attributions, size=(sample_img_tensor.shape[2], sample_img_tensor.shape[3]), mode="bilinear"
)

attr_np = attributions.squeeze().cpu().detach().numpy()
img_np = sample_img.squeeze().cpu().detach().numpy()

plt.figure(figsize=(10, 4))
plt.subplot(1, 2, 1)
plt.imshow(img_np, cmap="gray")
plt.title("Input Image")
plt.axis("off")

plt.subplot(1, 2, 2)
plt.imshow(img_np, cmap="gray")
plt.imshow(attr_np, cmap="jet", alpha=0.5)
plt.title("Grad-CAM Overlay")
plt.axis("off")

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
